  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (MRL 3)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. This package elevates the assessment to Model Risk Level 3 to reflect the expanded use of simulation results in a regulatory submission without parallel physical testing. Thirteen credibility factors are addressed; twelve are fully assessed and one (Use error) is recorded as not-assessed on the grounds that operator interaction with the CFD solver is considered outside the scope of the COU. The rationale argues the factor does not apply because post-processing is automated, but the encoding retains factorStatus 'not-assessed' rather than 'not-applicable', which materially weakens credibility at MRL 3.",
