      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted relative hemolysis index (RH) must agree with experimental measurements within combined simulation and experimental uncertainty at all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "RH predictions at all five operating points fall within the expanded uncertainty band (k=2) of experimental measurements. Mean absolute error is 7.2%. Worst-case underprediction at 6 L/min / 3500 RPM is 9.8%, within the 12% acceptance threshold. Required level 3 is met."
