      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence must be demonstrated via residual monitoring; residuals must drop at least four orders of magnitude and mass imbalance must be below 0.1%.",
      "rationale": "All simulations achieve six-order-of-magnitude reduction in continuity and momentum residuals. Mass imbalance is below 0.05% in all cases. Pseudo-transient continuation is used to improve convergence robustness. Required level 2 is met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "rationale": "The assessment team concluded that use error does not apply to this COU because all post-processing steps are fully automated via scripted Python pipelines with no manual operator intervention after boundary condition setup. Accordingly, no formal assessment of user-induced error was performed. The factor is recorded as not-assessed rather than not-applicable pending a formal scoping review by the quality assurance authority."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The turbulence model and hemolysis damage accumulation model must be justified for the flow regime and validated against independent data.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-omega turbulence model is selected based on published benchmark studies for rotating internal flows. The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model is used with coefficients calibrated against Heuser-Opitz data. Model form uncertainty is quantified via comparison with the Zhang et al. model; maximum RH difference is 6%. Required level 3 is met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties, geometric dimensions, and operating parameters must be sourced from calibrated measurements with stated uncertainties.",
      "rationale": "Blood viscosity and density are taken from published rheological measurements at 37°C with stated 2% uncertainty. Pump geometry is digitized from engineering drawings with dimensional tolerance of ±0.05 mm. Operating conditions are drawn from the FDA experimental protocol. Required level 2 is met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
